gomodel:SYNGO_4129  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Colocalisation of Arf6 with synaptophysin puncta in double-immunolabeling of primary hippocampal neurons is indicative of presynaptic localization.\n\n17/02/2021 Dnyanada: Figure S1B shows that Arf6 also colocalises with presynaptic marker VGlut1. Figure S3 shows that the anti-Arf6 antibody (AVIVA SYSTEM BIOLOGY, ARP54598-P050, 1:100) used in the study did not produce a signal in arf6-knockdown condition, and the effect was rescued indicating that the antibody might be specific for Arf6.\nArf6 also colocalises with postsynaptic marker \"homer\" and a separate annotation has been made for the term \"postsynapse\" (SynGO ID:4529). Experimental description: M&M\n\nHippocampal primary culture\n\nPregnant rats were killed by inhalation of CO2, and 18-day-old embryos were immediately removed by Cesarean section." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4129" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

